OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Bob
OL,4,CGravells
OL,6,F"The Captain called the gunners and
OL,7,Fcrew and he had a bottle there and he
OL,8,Fannounced that we were off to France,"
OL,9,FMr Gravells added.
OL,11,F"There were so many ships and people
OL,12,Ftransporting equipment, it was just
OL,13,Fhectic but we were just concerned
OL,14,Fabout our own little part."
OL,16,FErna had a sister ship which was also
OL,17,Fin the convoy and was hit and nearly
OL,18,Fsunk - when Erns arrived at the
OL,19,Fbeaches a German plane flew overhead.
